Paragraphs: The most genuine complaint we girls make every day is "I don't have anything to wear". The easiest way to not burn a hole in your pockets is by repurposing & reusing our outfits, but no one wants to be seen in the same clothes every 2 weeks. So, solve this forever pressuring problem with these simple fashion hacks to turn your old clothes into new easy effortless outfits and get going every day of the week with a cool new outfit! First and foremost, Have a big loose t-shirt that you never wear or a fringe top that looks big on you? Cut the t-shirt from the midsection in a vertical straight line & voila! You have a brand new shrug that you can pair with literally everything. You can do the same with a long Kurta too. The second one, Any dress can be revamped into looking something completely different from what it really is by just adding a broad belt of your choice. Not only does it repurpose your whole outfit but this hack reduces inches from your waist and makes your curves look amazing! You can do the same with your shirts.
